post_text: Aurora Elementary 4th grade students recently read a story about Yosemite National Park. They researched the park, created math word problems using their new vocabulary, and created slideshows and dioramas using the writing skills they've learned this year. Their dioramas are on display in the hallway so everyone can see their amazing work!

Dillsboro Elementary Teachers Ms. Craig, Mrs. Frank, Mrs. Hughes, Mrs. Pruss, and Miss Rogers held a special Parade last week! The teachers traveled nearly 100 miles through storms and rain to see their students at home and leave surprises for those who weren't available. They were sure to practice social distancing as shown in the pictures of them having fun. Mrs. Frank said it was "One of our best days ever!"

*Special thanks and photo credits to Jacob Frank for joining the entire parade to get a pic of each lucky teacher with her special student.

post_text: At South Dearborn Community School Corporation, we are proud of our innovative technology! We are fortunate to house several 3D printers at our schools, which are capable of printing all types of items from an assortment of materials. With the help of Five Star Technology, we were able to design and print 314 ear guards. These ear guards will be used by healthcare workers to protect their ears from the elastic straps of the face masks they are required to wear during their shifts. The 314 ear guards were recently donated to Highpoint Health Hospital in Lawrenceburg, Margaret Mary Hospital in Batesville, and Decatur County Hospital in Greensburg. From all of us at SDCSC, thank you to all our frontline workers, we greatly appreciate all you do for our community and beyond! Five Star Technology Solutions

These ear guards will be used by healthcare workers to protect their ears from the elastic straps of the face masks they are required to wear during their shifts. The 314 ear guards were recently donated to Highpoint Health Hospital in Lawrenceburg, Margaret Mary Hospital in Batesville, and Decatur County Hospital in Greensburg. From all of us at SDCSC, thank you to all our frontline workers, we greatly appreciate all you do for our community and beyond! Five Star Technology Solutions

Students, teachers, and staff at South Dearborn Community School Corporation have had to make many adjustments preparing to learn from home over the course of the next couple months. While eLearning days will keep us healthy and safe, we still will miss our students filling our classrooms with laughter and fun. In an effort to stay connected to those who matter most to us, we will be posting videos of SDCSC teachers and staff reading their favorite books to our students and community. Whether you use them as a story after family dinner or a way to take a break during the day, we hope you enjoy them!

Our first story is brought to you by Mrs. Batchelor, a teacher at Aurora Elementary School. She will be reading “Pig the Pug” by Aaron Blabey. Please comment below to let us know that you tuned in!

Clarification: Videos will be posted to the SDCSC page, not to individual school pages.

post_text: Eighth grade students from the South Dearborn Middle School Ceramics class had the opportunity to visit Queen City Clay in Cincinnati. With instruction from the Queen City Clay staff, students learned the basics of centering, opening, pulling, and shaping clay on the potter’s wheel. They are usually able to complete 3 to 4 pots in just 4 hours. #WeAreSD #GrowExcelAchieve

The hallways are now filled with winter cheer at AES!

"On Tuesday, November 19th, 2019 South Dearborn Community Schools will be closed in support of our many teachers and staff attending the "Red for Ed" Action Day in downtown Indianapolis.

Currently, we have a large number of staff members planning to attend this event. As a result, we are unable to obtain a sufficient amount of substitute teachers to ensure a safe and productive day of instruction.

We realize that closing school is an inconvenience for some families and hope that this early notification gives everyone sufficient time to make arrangements.

The make-up day will be on Monday, January 20, 2020, which was a previously scheduled snow make-up day."

Thank you,

SDCSC Administration

ICYMI: South Dearborn High School students now have the opportunity to join the Business Professionals of America (BPA) club!

Mrs. Kelly Pettit, a new Business Education teacher at SDHS took eleven of her students to Terre Haute for BPA’s Fall Leadership Conference at Indiana State University.

Thank you to Mrs. Pettit for not only getting these students involved with a great organization, but also showing them around one of Indiana’s fine public universities.

*BPA is a national organization with over 55,000 members and over 23,000 chapters in 23 states. There were 18 other schools in attendance at the conference at ISU.

shared_text:
South Dearborn High School
October 23, 2019 at 12:08 PM ·

‼️ATTENTION ALL STUDENTS‼️

You have a unique opportunity to learn about many of the colleges in our region! We are hosting a college fair today (October 23rd) from 6:30 - 8:00pm in the cafeteria. There will be over 60 colleges in attendance.

Bring your friends & family with you as you gauge which of these schools peak your interest and begin the first important step into planning your future!

If you're wondering which schools will be in attendance, the list will be on the TVs at lunch, or you can visit the guidance office to see the list posted on the windows.

post_text:
Earlier this month, our students learned all about being aware of their online presence during Digital Citizenship Week.

We live in a time where there is unlimited access to information and as the years go on, the youth are more exposed to the digital world than ever. That’s why it is so important to have good digital citizenship, and understand what that means.

During this week, the students were taught awareness of their digital footprint, learned how to identify fake vs. real news, were encouraged to keep a healthy balance of “online time” vs. “real world” time, and fought back against cyberbullying.

Here are some of our students getting into the spirit of Digital Citizenship Week and learning valuable lessons!

Our South Dearborn High School students truly are becoming amazing leaders right before our very eyes!

In this article by Eagle Country 99.3, our students are praised for their initiative in creating something that our amazing high school has needed for awhile: a National FFA Organization chapter.

While they aren’t an accredited chapter yet, we are fully confident that these students will get there soon!
